article.headline: Evansville 63, Cleveland State 49
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Bradley Strickland scored 17 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Evansville past Cleveland State 63-49 Saturday in the America's Youth Classic. Strickland shot 5-of-9 from the floor and 7-of-9 from the free-throw line for the Purple Aces (1-2). Evansville's Matt Webster added 15 points and hit 11 of 12 free throws. Cleveland State led 2-0 on a jumper from Raheem Moss but trailed the rest of the game. J'Nathan Bullock led Cleveland State (1-3) with 10 points on 3-of-10 shooting and nine rebounds. The Vikings shot just 18-of-58 (31 percent) from the floor and were outrebounded 36-34. The Vikings forced 13 turnovers which they turned into 15 points.
